==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spandrel
<hw>Span"drel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Span</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The irregular
triangular space between the curve of an arch and the inclosing right
angle; or the space between the outer moldings of two contiguous arches
and a horizontal line above them, or another arch above and inclosing
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A narrow mat or passe partout for a picture.</def>
<mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spane</ent>⟦br⟧
